<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>URL Shortener Server</h1>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>API</h2>
            <p>
                The URL shortener API is accessible at: <code>/api</code>
            </p>
            <p>
                You can use this API to programmatically create and retrieve short URLs.
                Here are some example endpoints:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Create Short URL: <code>POST /api</code></li>
                <li>Retrieve Original URL: <code>GET /api/:shortId</code></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>UI Shortener</h2>
            <p>
                The UI for the URL shortener is accessible at: <code>/UIshortener</code>
            </p>
            <p>
                You can use the UI to easily create and manage short URLs.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Additional Information</h2>
            <p>
                For more details or documentation, please refer to the project documentation.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
